# Build output. Everything in this directory is generated by `npm run build`
# in ../dev/ from sources under ../dev/src/. Netlify rebuilds on every push
# that touches ../dev/ or /blog/ (see ../netlify.toml) so committing build
# artifacts is unnecessary.
#
# A fresh clone needs `cd ../dev && npm install && npm run build` before
# this directory contains a deployable site.
#
# Source-of-truth for the three top-level non-page files (which look like
# content but are passed through unchanged) lives in:
#   ../dev/src/root-assets/_redirects
#   ../dev/src/root-assets/sitemap.xml
#   ../dev/src/root-assets/robots.txt

*
!.gitignore
